



✅ STAR Script 2 — Innovation After Rejection (Hackathon → Product → Patent)
Situation

I participated in a Qualcomm hackathon, but my initial proposal was rejected primarily due to privacy concerns and unclear business value.

Task

I needed to transform the concept into a viable, secure, and business-relevant solution.

Action

Collected detailed feedback from judges to understand gaps

Re-architected the solution to make privacy and secure camera buffer handling the core design principle

Strengthened business justification and practical production applicability

Proposed it internally as a formal feature request

Led the effort end-to-end, collaborating with multiple teams, defining trade-offs, and aligning execution

Result

Proposal was approved as a product-level feature

Progressed into internal innovation and patent review forums

Recognized with organization-level AI innovation acknowledgment

Demonstrated ability to convert rejection into high-impact innovation



Leadership Principles Shown: Invent and Simplify, Bias for Action, Think Big, Ownership, Earn Trust


